rComments: Professor Donnelly is a rare gem: so smart, approachable, and kind. He expects a lot from you (get ready to read), but funnily enough you want to impress him so you end up working really hard. His grading is fair but on the tough end of the spectrum. But his feedback is extensive and will tell you where you went wrong and how to fix those issues.
Professor Donnelly consistently provided clear lectures. He always made himself available to any questions or concerns I had. Professor Donnelly actually cares about the well-being of his students.

Professor Donnelly is a breath of fresh air in the highly competitive UofT setting. He is not only the kindest and most approachable professor that I have ever had, but he is also fair and clear in his teaching and marking. He made me fall in love with my major again and because of him I take pride in studying English literature!

Overall a great and empathic prof. Young guy who knows what every student is going through and respects that we have a lot to handle, so he is quite easy going. In 3rd year, and one of my best profs so far.
He's a super nice professor, and makes class inviting and warm!

I love this professor! He is he friendliest and sweetest professor ever. There is no professor that I liked better than him. He is always interested in hearing what you have to say and in class discussions are fun with him. He is extremely helpful and if you ever need some help from him, don't ever hesitate to ask because he will help for sure!
